---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('frequency');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Definition</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					The dynamic state of the tension continuum.
				</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Frequency</strong> is the engineering descriptor of the high-dimensional tension continuum in which identities exist and interact. It captures the spectrum of characteristic oscillation frequencies, resonance conditions and damping ratios that determine how an identity’s internal tension field evolves over time.
				</p>
				<p>
					At its core, every identity is defined by a fundamental tension: the ongoing negotiation between <strong class="text-white/80">Sameness</strong> (coherence, continuity of the stem) and <strong class="text-white/80">Causal Entropy</strong> (opening of future possibilities). Frequency makes this tension visible as a dynamic, multidimensional field rather than a simple binary opposition.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">The Inner Tension Field</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/55 mb-6">
					The tension an identity experiences is not a single force pulling in one direction. It is a high-dimensional field generated by multiple, often conflicting demands:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Sameness vs. Entropy</strong> — the foundational tension between preserving coherence and expanding possibilities.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Internal vs. External</strong> — tension arising from one’s own vision versus external expectations, relationships, and regulatory forces.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Stability vs. Expansion</strong> — the tension between maintaining current structure and the drive to grow or differentiate.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Resonance vs. Dissonance</strong> — tension created by alignment or misalignment with other identities and idea-fields.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="mt-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					Frequency is the tool that makes this multidimensional tension field describable and, to a certain degree, steerable.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Mechanics</div>
				<ul class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension field:</strong> The high-dimensional continuum of internal stress, deflection and competing demands an identity is permanently exposed to.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Frequency spectrum:</strong> The characteristic rates and patterns at which tension oscillates. These patterns reveal which tensions are dominant, which are amplifying, and which are decaying.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Resonance:</strong> When frequencies of different tension fields align, mutual amplification occurs. This can be highly productive (shared vision, strong relationships) or destructive (reinforcing dysfunctional patterns).
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Damping (general):</strong> The rate at which tension oscillations lose energy. Damping is a fundamental parameter of any tension field. Its higher-order, regulatory application at collective scale is developed in the Collective Identity layer (see Damping).
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Rotation and Tension</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/55 mb-6">
					Rotation has a double relationship to tension:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Stabilizing effect:</strong> Strong rotation around the Identity Stem increases resistance to small and medium disturbances (gyroscopic effect). This allows an identity to hold significantly more internal tension without losing its fundamental orientation.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension-generating effect:</strong> Rotation simultaneously creates its own centrifugal tension — a drive toward expansion, differentiation and, in extreme cases, fragmentation. This self-generated tension must be absorbed by sufficient Mass and internal cohesion.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="mt-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					Healthy high rotation therefore requires enough Mass to “hold” the centrifugal tension it produces. Without sufficient Mass, strong rotation shifts from stabilizing to fragmenting.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering work:</strong> Develop the capacity to read the current tension field of an identity (including its own generated tensions through rotation and mass creation) and to intervene deliberately through Frequency work — shaping resonance, applying targeted damping, and aligning internal cycles with supportive external fields.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="frequency" />
	</main>
</Layout>
